one thing that i have found to be my lifeblood in pvp so far is, deflection shields and reflection shield projectors (or whatever there called, one boosts AC and uses parry, other boosts somthing and uses riposte eheh) BwT, and my favorite thing to do, is before we start the duel, i cast my lotus on the water type spell (not sure which one im using right now, i think meditate on an autumn leaf) and then quickly sit out the 15 seconds of locked nano, use a nano recharger and then start the fight so i come in with full nano for healing, and the damage buff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/udragonflyao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dragonfly AO</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#660000>(2/25/02 12:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1694.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP tips with martial artists...</span><hr size=1> i am a lv 136 apprentice so what i say should have some validity. <br>
<br>
get run buffs whenever u can and keep run speed skill maxxed<br>
<br>
ma vs soldier: brawl , bwt , run away and heal urself if u havent died from fling burst and FA. when MA skill pops back up go bwt him again and brawl run away heal urself. rinse and repeat. <br>
<br>
ma vs agent: brawl bwt dimach and hope u can keep urself healed until DoT kills him cuz youll be rooted most of the fight. <br>
<br>
ma vs enforcer: brawl bwt run away BUT ! rage line makes enforcers super fast so when u run away run through a city area trying to lose them jumping over buildings and diving between small alleys and stuff. rinse and repeat when MA skill pops back up. <br>
<br>
ma vs mp: fight toe to toe, brawl dimach bwt and keep urself healed. the DoT will cancel out the pet heals so its all up to ur fists to finish him off. MPs 130+ are very tough tho pet heals for more.<br>
<br>
ma vs fixer: toe to toe brawl DoT heal self dimach if needed. <br>
<br>
ma vs trader: run as fast as u can to the zone and hope he hasnt gotten close enough to root you , then stay far away from the area you saw the trader in. <br>
<br>
ma vs ma: first laugh. then use what ever you want and try to keep ur hps full at all times. <br>
<br>
ma vs eng: sometimes u need to fight them toe to toe because some engs know how to reflect their pet heals off their pet onto themself. otherwise brawl DoT run away heal urself rinse and repeat. <br>
<br>
ma vs doctor: 75+ dont even bother just run to the zone and try not to get rooted. <br>
<br>
ma vs adv: toe to toe they might make u have to use dimach because their heals r faster then ours. <br>
<br>
ma vs crat: i have never fought a crat or seen one in a pvp zone so i cant say. <br>
<br>
ma vs NT: i wouldnt advise fighting one but if u have to,  dimach brawl and shen. dont even think about trying to kill one if u dont have shen. try to stay toe to toe and if rooted heal urself and hope DoT from shen kills him. <br>
<br>
It's not easy PvPing with MAs after lv 75+. I got Apprentice title at lv 70 or something like that but, I have lost it a couple of times and always got it back the next day. At lv 100 I lost apprentice and got it back. At lv 120 I lost apprentice and got it back. MAs suck for PvP I wont lie. PvPing with an MA takes alot more skill then PvPing with an enforcer or soldier. And the funny thing is I started an Enforcer because if patch doesn't fix us I will take my PvP know-how to the Enforcer profession and say &quot;bye-bye Dragonfly&quot;. Anyway hope my info helps a little, take care. <br>
